OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FSome mist and fog patches
OL,6,Fpossible to start. Turning brighter in
OL,7,Feastern parts of Wales. In the west,
OL,8,Fcloudy and breezy, with spots of
OL,9,Fdrizzle eventually pushing into the
OL,10,Frest of Wales. Mild for the time of
OL,11,Fyear.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FSimilar overnight. Often
OL,14,Fcloudy, breezy with spells of rain and
OL,15,Fdrizzle, often the most persistent
OL,16,Facross the Welsh hills. Another mild
OL,17,Fnight to come.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
